name: esterification of soybean oil | fatty acid methyl ester | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/3006/documentation

This dataset represents the production of soybean methyl ester, respectively glycerine, from crude soybean oil. Density = 0.88 kg/l

From reception of raw materials at the factory gate through esterification of crude soybean oil.

The dataset includes intermediate storage of the oil and products. System boundary is at the esterification plant.
category: C:Manufacturing/19:Manufacture of coke and refined petroleum products/192:Manufacture of refined petroleum products/1920:Manufacture of refined petroleum products

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Data for 2009; current technology for biodiesel plants.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data collected from National Biodiesel Board (NBB) North American members.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Typical vegetable oil esterification plant designed for the production of methyl ester (for use in the vehicle fuels market).
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Primary data - from National Biodiesel Board (NBB) members.  Data collected for a year's period.

exchanges.description: Soy biodiesel; produced from esterification of crude soybean oil.  Note that The mass balance shows 93 grams more input than output (2.4%), which can be expected since the data were sampled separately.
